{
  "page": "Miller's wife from Acorn Water",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">For the mother of Ramsay Snow, see <a href=\"/index.php/Miller%27s_wife\" title=\"Miller&#39;s wife\">Miller's wife</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\">Miller's wife</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Miller%E2%80%99s_Wife_of_Acorn_Water_by_Wodania.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"The Miller’s Wife of Acorn Water by Wodania.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/fa/The_Miller%E2%80%99s_Wife_of_Acorn_Water_by_Wodania.jpg/350px-The_Miller%E2%80%99s_Wife_of_Acorn_Water_by_Wodania.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"458\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/fa/The_Miller%E2%80%99s_Wife_of_Acorn_Water_by_Wodania.jpg/525px-The_Miller%E2%80%99s_Wife_of_Acorn_Water_by_Wodania.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/fa/The_Miller%E2%80%99s_Wife_of_Acorn_Water_by_Wodania.jpg/700px-The_Miller%E2%80%99s_Wife_of_Acorn_Water_by_Wodania.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>The miller's wife, holding the skulls of <a href=\"/index.php/Miller%27s_sons\" title=\"Miller&#39;s sons\">her dead sons</a>. Art by Wodania&#160;©</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Stark\" title=\"House Stark\">House Stark</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Northmen\" title=\"Northmen\">Northmen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\nthe <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">North</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/299_AC\" title=\"299 AC\">299&#160;AC</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Acorn_Water\" title=\"Acorn Water\">Acorn Water</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Spouse</th><td>\nMiller of <a href=\"/index.php/Acorn_Water\" title=\"Acorn Water\">Acorn Water</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Lover</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Miller%27s_sons\" title=\"Miller&#39;s sons\">Two young sons</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b>miller's wife from Acorn Water</b> is the wife of the miller of <a href=\"/index.php/Acorn_Water\" title=\"Acorn Water\">Acorn Water</a> near <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">North</a>. She has <a href=\"/index.php/Miller%27s_sons\" title=\"Miller&#39;s sons\">Two young sons</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Theories\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Theories</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Miller%27s_wife_from_Acorn_Water&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>She has big soft pillowy breasts with wide dark nipples, stretch marks on her belly, a sweet mouth, and a merry laugh.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a> has known her for years<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> and <a href=\"/index.php/Bedded\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bedded\">bedded</a> her several times, and thinks there was nothing special about her.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> However, he later recalls her features, and the way she would claw at his back while they had sex, but he cannot recall her name.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Miller%27s_wife_from_Acorn_Water&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Miller%27s_wife_from_Acorn_Water&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>After Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Rodrik_Cassel\" title=\"Rodrik Cassel\">Rodrik Cassel</a> captures \"<a href=\"/index.php/Ramsay_Snow\" title=\"Ramsay Snow\">Reek</a>\", his party stops at the mill for a while before continuing to Winterfell. The miller's wife sells them hay for their <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">horses</a>, and Ser Rodrik speaks with <a href=\"/index.php/Miller%27s_sons\" title=\"Miller&#39;s sons\">her sons</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a> leads <a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">ironborn</a> raiders to <a href=\"/index.php/Capture_of_Winterfell\" title=\"Capture of Winterfell\">capture Winterfell</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Rickon_Stark\" title=\"Rickon Stark\">Rickon Stark</a> become his prisoners and <a href=\"/index.php/Hostage\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hostage\">hostages</a>. '\"Reek\", freed from Winterfell's dungeons, swears himself to Theon.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Bran and Rickon apparently escape Winterfell. Theon gathers a search party, including Reek, Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Luwin\" title=\"Luwin\">Luwin</a>, and the kennelmaster <a href=\"/index.php/Farlen\" title=\"Farlen\">Farlen</a> and his <a href=\"/index.php/Dog\" title=\"Dog\">dogs</a>, but fails to track them down in the <a href=\"/index.php/Wolfswood\" title=\"Wolfswood\">wolfswood</a>. However, Reek tells Theon he has a feeling that the Stark boys are hiding at the mill, and secretly presents Theon with the boys' fine clothing he had brought along in a bag. Theon sends the rest of the search party back to Winterfell, except for Reek and three ironborn, <a href=\"/index.php/Aggar\" title=\"Aggar\">Aggar</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Gelmarr\" title=\"Gelmarr\">Gelmarr</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Gynir\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gynir\">Gynir</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>At the mill, Reek kills the miller's two sons, and when their mother begs Theon for mercy, Gelmarr cuts her down with one blow of his axe. The dead children are decapitated and their heads <a href=\"/index.php/Flaying\" title=\"Flaying\">skinned</a> and dipped in tar by Reek, and Theon dresses their bodies in the Stark children's finery. Theon returns to Winterfell and presents the heads and headless bodies as Bran and Rickon. Theon mounts their heads on the castle walls, and burns the bodies and clothing to bones and ashes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Later, Theon has a nightmare that he is having sex with the miller's wife again, but she has <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/vagina_dentata\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:vagina dentata\">teeth below</a>, and she both tears out his throat and bites off his manhood. Theon also dreams of the feast for King <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_I_Baratheon\" title=\"Robert I Baratheon\">Robert I Baratheon</a>'s arrival at Winterfell, but soon realizes he is dining with the dead, including the miller's wife.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Miller%27s_wife_from_Acorn_Water&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Having returned to Winterfell for <a href=\"/index.php/Wedding_of_Ramsay_Bolton_and_Arya_Stark\" title=\"Wedding of Ramsay Bolton and Arya Stark\">Ramsay Bolton's wedding</a>, a regretful Theon feels that the castle is full of <a href=\"/index.php/Ghosts\" title=\"Ghosts\">ghosts</a> for him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> He thinks of the old ghosts from the <a href=\"/index.php/Crypts_of_Winterfell\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Crypts of Winterfell\">crypts</a> and the younger ones that he had made himself, including the miller's wife from Acorn Water and her two young sons.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In the <a href=\"/index.php/Godswood_of_Winterfell\" title=\"Godswood of Winterfell\">godswood of Winterfell</a>, Theon sees Bran's face in the <a href=\"/index.php/Weirwood\" title=\"Weirwood\">weirwood</a> and momentarily thinks he is being haunted by his ghost, before recalling that they had not actually killed Bran and Rickon, but instead only miller's sons. He speaks aloud that he had to have two heads or he would have been mocked, and is overheard by <a href=\"/index.php/Holly\" title=\"Holly\">Holly</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Rowan\" title=\"Rowan\">Rowan</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Rowan accuses Theon of being a <a href=\"/index.php/Kinslayer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kinslayer\">kinslayer</a>, and Theon denies any relationship to Bran and Rickon while thinking to himself that the two children he killed were just some miller's sons. He thinks that he had known the miller's wife for years, and remembers that she had big heavy breasts, a sweet mouth, and a merry laugh, pleasures that he can never again experience.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Miller%27s_wife_from_Acorn_Water&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>\"Reek\"</b>: You know that old mill, sitting lonely on the <a href=\"/index.php/Acorn_Water\" title=\"Acorn Water\">Acorn Water</a>? We stopped there when I was being dragged to <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a> a captive. The miller's wife sold us hay for our <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">horses</a> while <a href=\"/index.php/Rodrik_Cassel\" title=\"Rodrik Cassel\">that old knight</a> clucked over <a href=\"/index.php/Miller%27s_sons\" title=\"Miller&#39;s sons\">her brats</a>. Might be the <a href=\"/index.php/Stark\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Stark\">Starks</a> are hiding there.<br />\n</p><p><b>Theon</b>: Why there? There are a dozen villages and <a href=\"/index.php/Holdfast\" title=\"Holdfast\">holdfasts</a> just as close.<br />\n</p>\n<b>\"Reek\"</b>: Why? Now that’s past knowing. But they’re there, I have a feeling.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;\"<a href=\"/index.php/Ramsay_Snow\" title=\"Ramsay Snow\">Reek</a>\" and <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Theon had forgotten her name, but he remembered her body, soft pillowy breasts and stretch marks on her belly, the way she clawed his back when he fucked her. Last night in his dream he had been in bed with her once again, but this time she had teeth above <i>and</i> <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/vagina_dentata\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:vagina dentata\">below</a>, and she tore out his throat even as she was gnawing off his manhood. It was madness. He'd seen her die too. <a href=\"/index.php/Gelmarr\" title=\"Gelmarr\">Gelmarr</a> had cut her down with one blow of his axe as she cried to Theon for mercy. <i>Leave me, woman. It was him who killed you, not me. And he's dead as well.</i><sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>He was <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">trapped here</a>, with the <a href=\"/index.php/Ghosts\" title=\"Ghosts\">ghosts</a>. The old ghosts from <a href=\"/index.php/Crypt_of_Winterfell\" title=\"Crypt of Winterfell\">the crypts</a> and the younger ones that he had made himself, <a href=\"/index.php/Mikken\" title=\"Mikken\">Mikken</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Farlen\" title=\"Farlen\">Farlen</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Gynir_Rednose\" title=\"Gynir Rednose\">Gynir Rednose</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Aggar\" title=\"Aggar\">Aggar</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Gelmarr_the_Grim\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gelmarr the Grim\">Gelmarr the Grim</a>, the miller's wife from <a href=\"/index.php/Acorn_Water\" title=\"Acorn Water\">Acorn Water</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Miller%27s_sons\" title=\"Miller&#39;s sons\">her two young sons</a>, and all the rest. <i>My work. My ghosts. They are all here, and they are angry.</i><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The two we killed were just some <a href=\"/index.php/Miller%27s_sons\" title=\"Miller&#39;s sons\">miller's sons</a>. Theon did not want to think about their mother. He had known the miller's wife for years, had even bedded her. Big heavy breasts with wide dark nipples, a sweet mouth, a merry laugh. Joys that I will never taste again.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Theories\">Theories</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Miller%27s_wife_from_Acorn_Water&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Theories\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>It has been speculated that Theon fathered the miller's wife's sons, or at least the youngest one, as he bedded the miller's wife several times. However, this conjecture is disputed: Theon never considers the possibility that the children are his, which may imply that he had sex with the woman after they were already born; a proof of this may be Theon remembering \"stretch marks on her belly\",<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> that could have come from childbirth.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Miller%27s_wife_from_Acorn_Water&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.4</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_50\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Chapter 50\">C